    {"ev_id": "ev-conf-0b29df78", "brief": {"key_ideas": ["Uncovers side channels in secure processors exploiting metadata — holistic security analysis", "Microarchitecture security should be examined holistically rather than separately for each component", "Performance optimizations using metadata create side channels when metadata states become observable", "Demonstrates that metadata used for performance (cache tags, TLB entries, prefetch hints) leaks information"], "relevance": "Relevant to the kernel's interaction with secure processor features. Metadata side channels affect how the kernel manages cache, TLB, and prefetch state — the kernel's performance optimizations (using metadata) may create security vulnerabilities. This motivates kernel-level metadata scrubbing on context switches. Published at ISCA.", "methodology": "ISCA. Metadata-based side channel analysis. Holistic secure processor security evaluation."}, "concepts": ["Translation Lookaside Buffer"], "claims": [{"kind": "FailureMode", "id_prefix": "fail", "name": "Processor metadata optimizations create side-channel leakage", "description": "Metadata used for performance optimization (cache tags, TLB entries, prefetch state) creates observable side channels in secure processors. Holistic security analysis reveals leakage across components that appear secure in isolation."}]},

